{{Cat main}}
{{Commons category|Constellations}}
{{Wiktionary category 2}}

[[Constellation]]s are groupings of stars as they are viewed, along a [[Sightline|line-of-sight]] at a constant [[azimuth]] and [[elevation]] in the [[sky]]. 

This category identifies the 88 constellations currently recognised (areas of the sky) by the [[International Astronomical Union]] (IAU), plus some further subcategories. 

For individual [[star]]s, see also the category [[:Category:Stars|Stars]].

