{{Infobox recurring event|name=<!--Uses page name if omitted-->|native_name=තරු සාදය|native_name_lang=[[Sinhalese]]|logo=Star_party_sri_lanka_logo.png|logo_caption=ad astra per aspera|genre=Astronomical Observation Competition|frequency=Annually|location=[[University of Peradeniya]]|country=[[Sri Lanka]]|years_active={{age|2004|01|30}}|first={{start date|2004|01|30}}|participants=School Students|organised=Anandian Astronomical Association,<br/> Astronomical Society of Mahamaya Girls' College.|status=active|website={{url|http://www.starparty.lk}}}}

'''''Star Party Sri Lanka''''', commonly known as the "Star Party" is an astronomical observation competition held in Sri Lanka since 2004<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.starparty.lk/|title=Star Party'20 {{!}} Sri Lanka® - The Largest Astronomy Event in South Asia|website=Star Party {{!}} Sri Lanka®|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-04}}</ref>. It is the longest-running inter-school astronomical observation competition in Sri Lanka. It happens annually at the University of Peradeniya premises typically in the first quarter of the year. However, in some years it was held in the other periods of the year due to various reasons. Star Party considered the most important event in the Sri Lankan amateur astronomical calendar.

== Observation competition ==

Star Party night sky observation competition is the main focus event of the entire Star Party. High school students from all around the country teamed up and compete for the title "Best school-based astronomical observation team of the year" and the Star Party challenge trophy. A team consist of 5 members from the same school and there can be maximum of two teams (namely A and B) can compete from one school. The competition held under 6 sections as follows<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skyandtelescope.com/astronomy-events/star-party-2019-kandy-sri-lanka/|title=Star Party 2019 {{!}} Kandy, Sri Lanka|website=Sky & Telescope|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-04}}</ref>, 

* Best in moon mapping.
* Best in planetary observation.
* Best in deep-sky observation and constellation mapping.
* Best in observational astronomy (Theory).
* Best in celestial measurements.
* Best in spot-test and viva round.

The highest-scoring team of each of those sections wins the sub-trophy for the respective titles. The team that has the highest total score for all these sections wins the Star Party Challenge trophy and crowned as the Champions of the Star Party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://astronomerswithoutborders.org/member-reports/4758-star-party-2019-kandy-sri-lanka-successfully-concluded.html|title=Star Party 2019 {{!}} Kandy, Sri Lanka - Successfully Concluded|website=astronomerswithoutborders.org|access-date=2020-02-04}}</ref>

